---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import CalculatorCard from '../components/CalculatorCard.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Technical Disclaimer | Battery Calculators" 
  description="Technical and legal disclaimer for calculators on BatteryCalculators.com."
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <div class="mb-12 border-b border-hairline pb-8">
      <span class="text-label-uppercase text-m-red text-xs block mb-4">CRITICAL USER SAFETY NOTICE</span>
      <h1 class="text-display-md text-primary mb-6">Engineering Disclaimer</h1>
      <p class="text-body-md text-body font-light">
        Please read this technical disclaimer carefully before utilizing any calculations or sizing layouts provided by this website.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="flex flex-col gap-8 text-body-md text-body font-light">
      
      <section>
        <CalculatorCard class="border border-m-red bg-surface-soft p-6">
          <h3 class="text-title-sm text-primary uppercase font-bold mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="text-m-red font-bold">IMPORTANT</span> NO CERTIFIED DESIGNS
          </h3>
          <p class="text-body-sm text-body">
            All calculations, formulas, output estimations, and suggested configurations displayed on Battery Calculators are for preliminary educational and sizing estimation purposes only. They do not constitute certified engineering plans, safety documentation, or compliance designs.
          </p>
        </CalculatorCard>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-title-lg text-primary uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">1. Verification Requirement</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          Battery storage design, high-current DC wiring, and grid arbitrage calculations involve significant physical hazards, including fire, electrocution, thermal runaway, and financial liability.
        </p>
        <p>
          You must verify all calculations with certified electrical, marine, or civil engineering professionals and reference official standards (such as NEC, NFPA 855, IEEE 1547, ISO 13297, or local building codes) before fabricating any packs or routing wires.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-title-lg text-primary uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">2. Accuracy and Assumptions</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          Calculators are based on idealized models (e.g. constant wire resistivity, linear temperature derating, simple calendar ageing). Real-world performance varies due to:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 flex flex-col gap-2 text-body-sm text-muted">
          <li>Wire contact resistance and terminal oxidation.</li>
          <li>Transient currents, surges, and inrush loads.</li>
          <li>Inverter dynamic efficiency curves and stand-by power draw.</li>
          <li>Non-uniform thermal gradients inside cell enclosures.</li>
          <li>Local utility tariff changes and demand peaks.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-title-lg text-primary uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">3. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          Battery Calculators and its developers accept no liability for damage, injury, system failures, fires, or financial losses caused by using these tools. Use of the tools is entirely at your own risk.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
